Initial work towards https://github.com/NuGet/NuGetGallery/issues/4941.

I wanted to get your take on the initial work to show repository url from the `<repository>` metadata in a package. I imagine there is follow up work. Open questions;

 * Is the RepositoryUrl column in nuget.org's Packages table currently empty? It doesn't look like this was beening populated on upload.
 * What should we do with the `commit`, `branch`, and `type` attributes? We could introduce some some inference. For example, if `repository.url == https://github.com/natemcmaster/CommandLineUtils` and `repository.commit == 311673414d6530d97c70871a60c1a26f924f0d17`, should the packages page could show this link: https://github.com/natemcmaster/CommandLineUtils/tree/311673414d6530d97c70871a60c1a26f924f0d17

@diverdan92 @anangaur
